<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2012/12/18/spring-roo-1-2-3-release-available">Spring Roo 1.2.3.RELEASE available</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="null?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Alan Stewart</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-12-18 08:28:00.0">December 18, 2012</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="502" href="/blog/2012/12/18/spring-roo-1-2-3-release-available#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>The Spring Roo team is pleased to announce the availability 1.2.3.RELEASE.&nbsp; This is the third maintenance release for 1.2 and includes fixes for a number of issues and includes support for Spring Framework 3.2.0. Please see the <a href="https://jira.springsource.org/issues/?jql=project%20%3D%20ROO%20AND%20resolution%20%3D%20Complete%20AND%20fixVersion%20%3D%20%221.2.3.RELEASE%22%20AND%20status%20%3D%20Resolved">change log</a> for a list of the bugs and improvements completed.</p>
<p>I hope you enjoy this new release!</p>
<p>Alan</p>
<p>Spring Roo Project Lead</p>
</div>
